reviews.text: This is hands down the best coffee shop in Hong Kong. All their coffee beverages are delicious and their service is second to none! Plus it’s cheaper than every other place in the area too! Can’t go wrong.

A flat-white with oat milk;
A cappuccino with oat milk, and
A creamy nutty latte with oat milk. 
Nerve calming! Good ambience!
A nice alternative to Starbucks on the top floor.

Great tasting coffee which isn't too big. I always get the flat white and maybe a slice of carrot cake which is a modest portion size (so you don't have a meal-sized snack with your drink). Friendly staff. There's a private place to sit (inside) and an nice open place (outside).

Payment is octopus or cash - no credit cards.
The iced latte was excellent! It’s a much better place than it might look like.
Good Cappuccino & yet at Starbucks prices. Not spacious cafe but quite cosy. Recommended.

result.formatted_address: 500 Hennessy Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: 希慎廣場

reviews.text:
One of many malls dotting Causeway Bay area. Its lobby has a high vertical clearance. Trendy crowd...maybe because there was an Avengers exhibition going on at the time of my visit.

Had some difficulty finding Marketplace but as it turned out, was called Jasons, which is located two floors below ground.

The building had separate entries for the shopping areas and the office/residential area.
Amazing department store with all that you need in it. Great shops and restaurants
Large shopping mall in central location, not easy or pleasant to walk around or navigate. There are better malls in HK.

The big bookstore alone is worthy for a visit. The food court is decent and the general selection of stores is nicely put together. Directly connected to the mass transit too so this location is hard to beat.

Great shopping mall with can different kind of shops, including fashion, books store, restaurants, and Apple store.
Unlike other shopping mall, their escalator can easily reach each floor.
And there is a sky garden located on 4/F, which is a great place for relaxing, and it's open from 10am to 10pm
